      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A cryptocurrency is a digital code-based unit of money. Crypto ownership records are stored on a decentralized, securely linked digital ledger often called a blockchain.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Defining crypto more broadly is a complex matter. It’s definitely not an actual currency, because it is very rarely used as legal tender to buy or sell items —it’s highly likely that ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
