            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://bigthink.com/surprising-science/how-ramen-noodles-beat-cigarettes-to-become-a-prison-currency/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " are currently used by more people to regularly barter for daily goods and services. Crypto is also not a security, because it’s not attached to any underlying asset like stocks or bonds. Crypto may be most similar to gold or other commodities, because of its finite nature and the resources, time, and labor that it takes to “mine” it — but cryptos’ values can shift far more rapidly. In just the past year, there have been two Bitcoin ",
            "type": "text",
