        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Advocates of crypto say it is a boon to personal privacy. After all, because of the anonymous nature of the blockchain, it’s far easier to move digital money around without surveillance than it is in say, the U.S. banking system, which is tightly monitored, thanks to the USA PATRIOT Act. Crypto fans also say the decentralized nature of the currencies allows for greater wealth distribution. As billionaire venture capitalist Tim Draper ",
